						               													<description>Hurray, your company just got a lucrative job: build a road between two cities.&amp;#10;But the computer managing the production line just went bananas and random building material comes out of the factory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You already heard this story? Yes, but now it is multiplayer!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Going Further is a fast tile laying game for 1 to 4 players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player build his own road by joining tiles picked from a common set called &amp;quot;Tile Factory&amp;quot;. &amp;#10;The tiles in the Tile Factory are visible to all players.  &amp;#10;Beware that not all the tiles in the Tile Factory are immediately available to be played. Some of them can be unlocked only after other tiles have been selected and connected to a road. So, be fast to get to that valuable tile faster than your opponents!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when no more playable tiles are available.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player shall choose the best strategy to unlock new tiles while scoring as many points as possible and, at the same time, preventing the opponents to do the same.. &amp;#10;In fact, each tile grants a different number of points; the total score consists of the sum of each individual tile points.&amp;#10;Additional points can be added or removed from the total, depending on the achieved road final configuration.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In particular, watch out for road loops and famous landmarks!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
